<br>
Thank you Glatius.  Nice to think that maybe some people are seeing my points, and understanding them.<br>
<br>
The highest-end game is not something I can speak to, being as I'm only level 52.  But I understand from high-level paladins whom I respect that warriors do indeed have problems in xp groups at level 60 where everyone has high-end gear.<br>
<br>
I don't know what to do to fix that.  Improvements to taunt have been suggested, but I wouldn't be comfortable with them going in prior to level 60 if mitigation were put in to make warriors better than all other tanks.  Since a paladin at level 60 with a few AA points and some high end gear probably could be a group healer, I think warriors should DEFINITELY have their taunt abilities improved at that point, since paladins are able to fill TWO roles in xp groups at that stage of the game.<br>
<br>
Does any of that make sense?  I have a terrible head cold, and might not be making myself clear...<br>
<br>
