What I think that you don't quite understand is that what you are referring to is part of the penality for being a class that is part fighter and part caster. You're not supposed to have the full functions of both the figher and the caster. If you get the dammed hybrid thinking out of your head, you can perhaps see it this way -<br>
<br>
If I walk into Sebilis and decide I am going to Disco, those frogloks are not exactly good but they are not exactly evil either. Considering this, I *SHOULD* prefer a warrior to a paladin because the warrior is an all purpose equally good against everything guy. While the paladin could do the job, I don't need any of his special abilities and the warrior is the better tank overall.<br>
<br>
However if I decide I want to go to the Crypt instead, which is full of nasty undead things, I should prefer a paladin over a warrior as the paladin should be a specialist in this area.<br>
<br>
When a paladin is viewed in this manner, one can say - yea, they should be complete badasses against undead things and just ok against other stuff, while the warrior is equal good against everything.<br>
