<br>
No Xzander, they don't if you understand basic math, because you are thinking in terms of static numbers.<br>
Example.<br>
If a Monk had 2k hp and warrior had 3k, the monk has two thirds the hp of the warrior.<br>
After all the 125 hp items, say a warrior had 6k and a monk had 5k, now the monk has around 85% the hp of the warrior.  It gets even smaller with knights because of PE.<br>
<br>
Now, that 20% gain in monk hp is offset by what? A 50% gain in damage output since it now does 70% more damage than a warrior.<br>
<br>
Hmm...when you look at it this way, you see that it isn't as balanced as you would think.<br>
<br>
